commit.message:
Fixed AST::Node#updated to always return a copy. (#25)

Previously it relied on a call chain #initialize -> #freeze that returns `self`.
However, overriding constructor in a custom subclass and returning something else breaks `updated`.

commit.message:
bump rake

Fixes a deprecation warning on Ruby 2.7.0

```
$ bundle exec rake
/home/user/.rbenv/versions/2.7.0/lib/ruby/gems/2.7.0/gems/rake-10.5.0/lib/rake/application.rb:381: warning: deprecated Object#=~ is called on Proc; it always returns nil
...
```

See https://github.com/ruby/rake/issues/308

Only ship the necessary library files in the gem artifact

This limits the files that are shipped to those that are in the lib dir
and the readme/license files. This reduces the install size of the gem
for users.

Signed-off-by: Tim Smith <tsmith@chef.io>

Add to_sexp_array method to AST::Node.

This is useful e.g. for serializing AST to JSON.
Tweak the wording in the doc comment

Use `alias` for definition of `AST::Node#to_a`

By this change, the method will be faster around 33%.

Benchmark
--------

```
$ time ruby -rast -e 'node = AST::Node.new(:foo, [1,2,3,4,5]); 100000000.times{node.to_a}'
```

Result
-----

|     | before | after |
| --- | ------ | ----- |
| 1st | 4.47   | 2.89  |
| 2nd | 4.10   | 3.03  |
| 3rd | 4.56   | 2.75  |
| 4th | 4.57   | 2.84  |
| 5th | 4.15   | 3.13  |
| avg | 4.37   | 2.928 |

Note
-----

The method is small, but it is called many times by applications(e.g.  RuboCop). So, I think this change makes sense.

Fix building on Travis

- Take 1.8.7 and rbx-2 out of CI
- Specify patch version for Ruby 2.4.1

Fix a deprecation warning of simpleCov

`SimpleCov::Formatter::MultiFormatter[]` is deprecated.
So, this PR replaces it with `.new`.
See https://github.com/colszowka/simplecov/blob/cb0e62b37b63816d07bdb15f3ee88ceade0947e5/lib/simplecov/formatter/multi_formatter.rb#L27
correct Mixin module constant in code example (#13)

Upgrade Travis to newer bundler.

Necessary because of https://github.com/bundler/bundler/issues/3558.
